The Herald Sports Reporter TENNIS Zimbabwe have announced their Davis Cup team to face Uruguay next week in the World Group II Play-off at Harare Sports Club. The team is made up of the Lock brothers â€“ Benjamin and Courtney, Mehluli Sibanda and Benedict Badza. Takanyi Garanganga comes in as the new captain. He takes over from Freeman Nyamunokora. TZ also named their development squad consisting of Shane Tapera, Takura Muhwandagara, Ronan Mtisi and Thomu Thompson. The tie is on February 3 and 4.